17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
19 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
20 The purpose of this act is:
21 1. To establish a grace period of fourteen (14) days for the
22 processing and completion of required professional development hours
23 for child care professionals, ensuring that administrative delays do
24 not negatively impact their employment status or certification; and
HB1667 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 2. To ensure child care professionals have adequate time to
2 procure training in order to remain in compliance with the Child
3 Care Licensing Act and applicable administrative rules.
4 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
5 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 405.6 of Title 10, unless there
6 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
7 A. A grace period of fourteen (14) days shall be granted to all
8 child care professionals to submit the required documentation for
9 the completion of their annual professional development training
10 hours as defined in Section 402 of this title.
11 B. During this grace period, the child care professional shall
12 remain in compliance with licensing and employment requirements.
13 C. Employers and regulatory agencies shall not impose
14 penalties, suspensions, or employment terminations solely based on
15 the pending processing of professional development hours during the
16 grace period.
17 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 405.7 of Title 10, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 The Department of Human Services shall ensure that the review
21 period for early childhood education provider training applications
22 is no greater than fourteen (14) days.
